{{ config(
    unique_key = '_pk',
    cluster_by = ['charge_added_date', 'salesforce_account_id', 'product']
) }}

-- Extract all rate plan charges from the snapshot for all LLC accounts
WITH base_data AS (
    SELECT
        rate_plan_charge_id
        , subscription_id
        , salesforce_account_id
        , salesforce_entity_id
        , product
        , rate_plan_name
        , charge_number
        , subsidiary
        , arr_dollars
        , effective_start_date
        , effective_end_date
        , dbt_valid_from::DATE AS charge_added_date
        , COALESCE(dbt_valid_to::DATE, effective_end_date::DATE) AS charge_dropped_date
    FROM {{ ref('core_dim_zuora_contract_subscriptions_snapshot') }}
    WHERE subsidiary = '100 - Carta - LLC'
        AND arr_dollars != 0
        AND salesforce_account_id IS NOT NULL
),

-- Add previous charge_dropped_date to identify gaps in charge history
ordered_data AS (
    SELECT
        *
        , LAG(charge_dropped_date) OVER (
            PARTITION BY rate_plan_charge_id
            ORDER BY charge_added_date
        ) AS prev_dropped_date
    FROM base_data
),

-- Flag when a new group starts (gap between prev_dropped_date and charge_added_date)
grouped_data AS (
    SELECT
        *
        , CASE 
            WHEN prev_dropped_date IS NULL 
                OR charge_added_date > prev_dropped_date THEN 1
            ELSE 0
          END AS is_new_group
    FROM ordered_data
),

-- Assign group numbers to continuous charge periods
grouped_with_numbers AS (
    SELECT
        *
        , SUM(is_new_group) OVER (
            PARTITION BY rate_plan_charge_id
            ORDER BY charge_added_date 
            ROWS UNBOUNDED PRECEDING
        ) AS group_number
    FROM grouped_data
),

-- Consolidate continuous charge periods into single records (matches escalator model logic)
final_charges AS (
    SELECT
        rate_plan_charge_id
        , subscription_id
        , salesforce_account_id
        , salesforce_entity_id
        , product
        , rate_plan_name
        , charge_number
        , subsidiary
        , arr_dollars
        , MIN(charge_added_date) AS charge_added_date
        , MAX(charge_dropped_date) AS charge_dropped_date
    FROM grouped_with_numbers
    GROUP BY
        rate_plan_charge_id
        , subscription_id
        , salesforce_account_id
        , salesforce_entity_id
        , product
        , rate_plan_name
        , charge_number
        , subsidiary
        , group_number
        , arr_dollars
),

-- Get all UpdateProduct order events with their ARR values (pre-escalator)
update_product_orders AS (
    SELECT
        z.rate_plan_charge_id
        , z.salesforce_account_id
        , z.product
        , z.charge_number
        , z.rate_plan_name
        , z.arr_dollars AS update_product_arr
        , z.effective_start_date AS update_date
        , z.created_at
        , z.order_type
    FROM {{ ref('core_dim_zuora_subscriptions') }} z
    WHERE z.order_type = 'UpdateProduct'
        AND z.subsidiary = '100 - Carta - LLC'
),

-- Find the first RenewSubscription event after each UpdateProduct to determine cutoff date
renewal_orders AS (
    SELECT
        z.charge_number
        , z.effective_start_date
        , MIN(z.created_at) AS first_renewal_at
    FROM {{ ref('core_dim_zuora_subscriptions') }} z
    WHERE z.order_type = 'RenewSubscription'
        AND z.subsidiary = '100 - Carta - LLC'
    GROUP BY z.charge_number, z.effective_start_date
),

-- Combine UpdateProduct with renewal timing to set search window for snapshot
update_with_renewal_date AS (
    SELECT
        up.*
        , COALESCE(ren.first_renewal_at::DATE, up.update_date + 30) AS renewal_cutoff_date
    FROM update_product_orders up
    LEFT JOIN renewal_orders ren
        ON up.charge_number = ren.charge_number
        AND up.update_date = ren.effective_start_date
),

-- Find the first snapshot added after UpdateProduct (determines as_of_date for mart)
snapshot_at_renewal AS (
    SELECT
        uwr.charge_number
        , uwr.update_date
        , uwr.renewal_cutoff_date
        , fc.charge_added_date
        , fc.charge_added_date + 1 AS as_of_date
    FROM update_with_renewal_date uwr
    JOIN final_charges fc
        ON uwr.charge_number = fc.charge_number
        AND fc.charge_added_date >= uwr.update_date
        AND fc.charge_added_date <= uwr.renewal_cutoff_date
    QUALIFY ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY uwr.charge_number, uwr.update_date ORDER BY fc.charge_added_date) = 1
),

-- Get ARR value immediately before the UpdateProduct event
pre_update_arr AS (
    SELECT
        uwr.charge_number
        , uwr.update_date
        , fc.arr_dollars AS pre_update_arr
    FROM update_with_renewal_date uwr
    JOIN final_charges fc
        ON uwr.charge_number = fc.charge_number
        AND fc.charge_dropped_date <= uwr.update_date
    QUALIFY ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY uwr.charge_number, uwr.update_date ORDER BY fc.charge_dropped_date DESC) = 1
),

-- Calculate organic_raw per charge: UpdateProduct ARR - Pre-Update ARR
organic_calculation AS (
    SELECT
        sar.as_of_date AS charge_added_date
        , up.salesforce_account_id
        , up.product
        , up.charge_number
        , up.rate_plan_name
        , pre.pre_update_arr
        , up.update_product_arr
        , up.update_product_arr - COALESCE(pre.pre_update_arr, 0) AS organic_expansion_dollars
    FROM update_with_renewal_date up
    JOIN snapshot_at_renewal sar
        ON up.charge_number = sar.charge_number
        AND up.update_date = sar.update_date
    LEFT JOIN pre_update_arr pre
        ON up.charge_number = pre.charge_number
        AND up.update_date = pre.update_date
    WHERE up.update_product_arr IS NOT NULL
        AND up.update_product_arr != 0
        AND pre.pre_update_arr IS NOT NULL
),

-- Aggregate organic expansion by product
product_level AS (
    SELECT
        charge_added_date
        , salesforce_account_id
        , product
        , SUM(pre_update_arr) AS total_pre_update_arr
        , SUM(update_product_arr) AS total_update_product_arr
        , SUM(organic_expansion_dollars) AS total_organic_expansion_dollars
    FROM organic_calculation
    GROUP BY charge_added_date, salesforce_account_id, product
),

-- Aggregate organic expansion for "All LLC Products"
all_products AS (
    SELECT
        charge_added_date
        , salesforce_account_id
        , 'All LLC Products' AS product
        , SUM(pre_update_arr) AS total_pre_update_arr
        , SUM(update_product_arr) AS total_update_product_arr
        , SUM(organic_expansion_dollars) AS total_organic_expansion_dollars
    FROM organic_calculation
    GROUP BY charge_added_date, salesforce_account_id
),

unioned_records AS (
    SELECT * FROM product_level
    WHERE total_organic_expansion_dollars != 0

    UNION ALL

    SELECT * FROM all_products
    WHERE total_organic_expansion_dollars != 0
)

SELECT
    {{ dbt_utils.generate_surrogate_key([
        'charge_added_date',
        'salesforce_account_id',
        'product'
    ]) }} AS _pk
    , charge_added_date
    , salesforce_account_id
    , product
    , total_pre_update_arr
    , total_update_product_arr
    , total_organic_expansion_dollars
FROM unioned_records
ORDER BY charge_added_date

source .env && poetry run snow sql --query "
WITH organic_grain AS (
    SELECT 
        salesforce_account_id,
        product,
        charge_added_date,
        COUNT(*) as row_count
    FROM DEV_KLAJDI_ZIAJ_DB.DBT_CORE.core_fct_zuora_arr_organic_expansion_llc
    GROUP BY 1, 2, 3
    HAVING COUNT(*) > 1
),
mart_grain AS (
    SELECT 
        salesforce_account_id,
        product,
        as_of_date,
        COUNT(*) as row_count
    FROM DEV_KLAJDI_ZIAJ_DB.DBT_MART.mart_arr_zuora_delta_expansion_detailed_llc
    GROUP BY 1, 2, 3
    HAVING COUNT(*) > 1
)
SELECT 
    'organic_expansion' as model,
    COUNT(*) as duplicate_grain_count
FROM organic_grain
UNION ALL
SELECT 
    'mart_expansion_detailed' as model,
    COUNT(*) as duplicate_grain_count
FROM mart_grain
;" --format JSON
input.description: Check grain of both models in dev

content.thinking: Great! No grain violations in either model. Now let me verify that the join between the two models doesn't create multiple matches (many-to-one join).

input.command:
source .env && poetry run snow sql --query "
WITH mart_base AS (
    SELECT 
        salesforce_account_id,
        product,
        as_of_date,
        _pk
    FROM DEV_KLAJDI_ZIAJ_DB.DBT_MART.mart_arr_zuora_delta_expansion_detailed_llc
    WHERE arr_delta_day != 0
),
organic_counts AS (
    SELECT 
        salesforce_account_id,
        product,
        charge_added_date AS as_of_date,
        COUNT(*) as organic_row_count
    FROM DEV_KLAJDI_ZIAJ_DB.DBT_CORE.core_fct_zuora_arr_organic_expansion_llc
    GROUP BY 1, 2, 3
),
join_check AS (
    SELECT 
        m._pk,
        m.salesforce_account_id,
        m.product,
        m.as_of_date,
        o.organic_row_count
    FROM mart_base m
    LEFT JOIN organic_counts o
        ON m.salesforce_account_id = o.salesforce_account_id
        AND m.product = o.product
        AND m.as_of_date = o.as_of_date
)
SELECT 
    'max_organic_matches_per_mart_row' as check_type,
    MAX(COALESCE(organic_row_count, 0)) as value
FROM join_check
UNION ALL
SELECT 
    'mart_rows_with_multiple_organic_matches' as check_type,
    COUNT(*) as value
FROM join_check
WHERE organic_row_count > 1
;" --format JSON

content.thinking:
Perfect! The join is clean:
- Maximum of 1 organic expansion row matches per mart row
- 0 mart rows have multiple organic expansion matches

[Detailed prompt about analyzing ARR decomposition for LLC products]

Key requirements:
- Account: 0014T00000Oz7gQQAR
- Date: 2025-07-02
- Expected organic_raw: $2,750 (from ARR Delta $4,132.5 - Escalator $1,382.5)

```

```
no I mean from the source, so I see update_product_charges cte so basically similar to the core_fct_zuora_arr_escalator_llc model

give me an executable query so I can paste in snowflake.

all of these charges are the first time that they actually have the subscription...how can we dynamically remove this?

input.content:
# Organic Raw Expansion Calculation Logic

**Model:** `core_fct_zuora_arr_organic_expansion_llc`  
**Mart Column:** `arr_delta_organic_raw_expansion` in `mart_arr_zuora_delta_expansion_detailed_llc`  
**Date:** November 2025

---

## Overview

**Organic Raw Expansion** captures ARR growth that comes from customers upgrading their subscription tier or increasing their stakeholder count within the same product, *before* any escalator pricing is applied.

This is distinct from:
- **Escalator**: Automatic price increases built into contracts
- **Discount Changes**: ARR changes due to discounts being applied or removed
- **New Sales**: Brand new subscriptions (not upgrades)

---

## Business Definition

Organic raw expansion answers the question:  
**"How much more ARR did we gain because a customer upgraded their plan (more stakeholders, higher tier, etc.)?"**

### Example Scenario

**Customer:** ABC Company  
**Product:** LLC Cap Table  
**Date:** July 2, 2025

**Before Upgrade:**
- 50 stakeholders @ base pricing
- ARR: $10,000

**UpdateProduct Event (Tier Upgrade):**
- Customer upgrades to 100 stakeholders
- New ARR (pre-escalator): $12,750

**Organic Raw Expansion Calculation:**
```
$12,750 (new ARR) - $10,000 (old ARR) = $2,750 organic raw expansion
```

If there's also an escalator charge that adds $1,382.50, the total ARR increase would be:
```
$2,750 (organic) + $1,382.50 (escalator) = $4,132.50 total ARR delta
```

---

## Technical Calculation Logic

### Step 1: Consolidate Subscription Snapshots

We use daily snapshots of Zuora subscription charges and group them into continuous periods:
- Identify when charges are added (`dbt_valid_from`)
- Identify when charges are dropped (`dbt_valid_to` or `effective_end_date`)
- Group continuous charge periods (handles scenarios where the same charge appears across multiple snapshots)

**Why:** A single rate plan charge can appear in multiple snapshot days. We consolidate these into one continuous period to avoid counting the same charge multiple times.

### Step 2: Identify UpdateProduct Events

Find all Zuora orders with `order_type = 'UpdateProduct'`:
- These represent tier changes, stakeholder count increases, etc.
- Capture the ARR value at the time of the UpdateProduct event (pre-escalator)

**Key Detail:** We look for the first snapshot that appears *after* the UpdateProduct date but *before* the next renewal. This represents the "as_of_date" when the change takes effect in our mart.

### Step 3: Get Pre-Update ARR

For each UpdateProduct event, find the ARR value immediately *before* the update:
- Look backward in the snapshot history
- Get the most recent charge ARR before the UpdateProduct date

**Filter:** We exclude UpdateProduct events where there's no prior ARR history (these represent first-time subscriptions, not upgrades).

### Step 4: Calculate Organic Expansion

```
Organic Raw Expansion = UpdateProduct ARR - Pre-Update ARR
```

**Filters Applied:**
- Only include LLC subsidiary charges (`subsidiary = '100 - Carta - LLC'`)
- Exclude first-time subscriptions (where `pre_update_arr IS NULL`)
- Exclude zero-value changes (where `organic_expansion_dollars = 0`)
- Only include charges where `arr_dollars != 0`

### Step 5: Aggregate by Product

Sum organic expansion amounts for:
1. **Product-level:** Individual products (e.g., "LLC Cap Table", "LLC Transfer Agent")
2. **All LLC Products:** Rollup across all LLC products for a given account and date

---

## Data Sources

### Primary Source: Zuora Contract Subscriptions Snapshot
**Table:** `dbt_snapshots.core_dim_zuora_contract_subscriptions_snapshot`

**Key Fields:**
- `rate_plan_charge_id`: Unique charge identifier
- `subscription_id`: Zuora subscription ID
- `salesforce_account_id`: Customer account ID
- `product`: Product name
- `arr_dollars`: Annual recurring revenue for the charge
- `dbt_valid_from`: When the charge snapshot became active
- `dbt_valid_to`: When the charge snapshot became invalid (NULL if still active)
- `effective_start_date`: Contract effective start date
- `effective_end_date`: Contract effective end date

### Secondary Source: Zuora Subscriptions (Orders)
**Table:** `core_dim_zuora_subscriptions`

**Key Fields:**
- `order_type`: Type of order (we filter for 'UpdateProduct')
- `charge_number`: Links back to rate plan charges
- `effective_start_date`: When the order takes effect
- `created_at`: When the order was created in Zuora

---

## Output Granularity

**Grain:** One row per `(salesforce_account_id, product, charge_added_date)`

### Output Columns:
- `_pk`: Primary key (hash of account, product, date)
- `charge_added_date`: Date when the organic expansion occurred
- `salesforce_account_id`: Customer account
- `product`: Product name (or "All LLC Products")
- `total_pre_update_arr`: Total ARR before the UpdateProduct event
- `total_update_product_arr`: Total ARR from the UpdateProduct order
- `total_organic_expansion_dollars`: Calculated organic expansion (difference)

---

## Edge Cases Handled

### 1. First-Time Subscriptions
**Scenario:** Customer signs up for a new product  
**Handling:** Excluded via `pre_update_arr IS NOT NULL` filter  
**Rationale:** This is "New Business", not organic expansion

### 2. Multiple UpdateProduct Events Same Day
**Scenario:** Customer upgrades multiple charges on the same date  
**Handling:** Aggregated at the product level  
**Result:** Single row with summed organic expansion for that account-product-date

### 3. Renewal Between UpdateProduct Events
**Scenario:** Customer renews subscription after an UpdateProduct  
**Handling:** Use first renewal date as cutoff for finding snapshot  
**Rationale:** Ensures we capture the expansion at the right point in time

### 4. Charges with Zero ARR
**Scenario:** Rate plan charges with $0 ARR  
**Handling:** Excluded from source data  
**Rationale:** No revenue impact to track

### 5. Floating Point Precision
**Scenario:** ARR calculations with many decimals  
**Handling:** Accepted (differences typically < 0.00001)  
**Validation:** Components sum to total ARR delta within floating point precision

---

## Integration with Mart

The organic expansion model feeds into `mart_arr_zuora_delta_expansion_detailed_llc`:

```sql
-- Mart adds this column:
arr_delta_organic_raw_expansion

-- Joined on:
- salesforce_account_id
- product  
- as_of_date (matches charge_added_date from organic model)
```

### Mart Validation
Total ARR delta should equal the sum of components:
```
arr_delta_day = 
    arr_delta_escalator 
    + arr_delta_organic_raw_expansion 
    + arr_delta_total_discount_impact
```

**Current Results:**
- 7,710 total mart rows
- 1,269 rows with organic expansion (16.5%)
- All components sum correctly (validated ‚úÖ)

---

## Use Cases

### 1. Product Analytics
Track which products are seeing the most organic growth from customer upgrades.

### 2. Customer Success Metrics
Identify customers who are expanding their usage (good retention signal).

### 3. Revenue Attribution
Break down ARR changes into escalator vs. organic vs. discount components.

### 4. Sales Compensation
Potentially use organic expansion as a metric for account manager compensation.

### 5. Forecasting
Better predict ARR growth by separating organic expansion from contractual escalators.

---

## Example Query

```sql
-- Get top 10 accounts by organic expansion in 2025
SELECT 
    salesforce_account_id,
    product,
    SUM(total_organic_expansion_dollars) as total_organic_expansion,
    COUNT(*) as expansion_events
FROM prod_db.dbt_core.core_fct_zuora_arr_organic_expansion_llc
WHERE charge_added_date >= '2025-01-01'
GROUP BY 1, 2
ORDER BY 3 DESC
LIMIT 10;
```

---

## Limitations & Considerations

### 1. LLC Subsidiary Only
Currently only tracks LLC products. Other subsidiaries (Inc, International) would need separate models.

### 2. Pre-Escalator Values
Organic expansion is calculated *before* escalator pricing. The escalator component is tracked separately in `core_fct_zuora_arr_escalator_llc`.

### 3. Snapshot Dependency
Relies on daily snapshots being run consistently. Gaps in snapshot data could lead to missing expansion events.

### 4. UpdateProduct Events Only
Only captures expansion from Zuora UpdateProduct orders. Other expansion mechanisms (e.g., adding new products) are tracked differently.

### 5. Date Convention
Uses `charge_added_date + 1` to match mart's `as_of_date` convention (expansion shows up the day after it's added to the snapshot).

---

## Questions?

For technical questions about the model:
- **Model Location:** `models/models_scratch/core/zuora/intermediate/llc_decomp/`
- **Jira Ticket:** [DA-4049](https://carta1.atlassian.net/browse/DA-4049)
- **GitHub PR:** [#8938](https://github.com/carta/ds-dbt/pull/8938)

For business questions about organic expansion metrics:
- Contact: Data Analytics team or Product Analytics

**Mart Column:** `arr_delta_organic_raw_expansion` in `mart_arr_zuora_delta_expansion_detailed_llc`  
**Date:** November 2025

---

## Overview

**Organic Raw Expansion** captures ARR growth that comes from customers upgrading their subscription tier or increasing their stakeholder count within the same product, *before* any escalator pricing is applied.

This is distinct from:
- **Escalator**: Automatic price increases built into contracts
- **Discount Changes**: ARR changes due to discounts being applied or removed
- **New Sales**: Brand new subscriptions (not upgrades)

---

## Business Definition

Organic raw expansion answers the question:  
**"How much more ARR did we gain because a customer upgraded their plan (more stakeholders, higher tier, etc.)?"**

### Example Scenario

**Customer:** ABC Company  
**Product:** LLC Cap Table  
**Date:** July 2, 2025

**Before Upgrade:**
- 50 stakeholders @ base pricing
- ARR: $10,000

**UpdateProduct Event (Tier Upgrade):**
- Customer upgrades to 100 stakeholders
- New ARR (pre-escalator): $12,750

**Organic Raw Expansion Calculation:**
```
$12,750 (new ARR) - $10,000 (old ARR) = $2,750 organic raw expansion
```

If there's also an escalator charge that adds $1,382.50, the total ARR increase would be:
```
$2,750 (organic) + $1,382.50 (escalator) = $4,132.50 total ARR delta
```

---

## Technical Calculation Logic

### Step 1: Consolidate Subscription Snapshots

We use daily snapshots of Zuora subscription charges and group them into continuous periods:
- Identify when charges are added (`dbt_valid_from`)
- Identify when charges are dropped (`dbt_valid_to` or `effective_end_date`)
- Group continuous charge periods (handles scenarios where the same charge appears across multiple snapshots)

**Why:** A single rate plan charge can appear in multiple snapshot days. We consolidate these into one continuous period to avoid counting the same charge multiple times.

### Step 2: Identify UpdateProduct Events

Find all Zuora orders with `order_type = 'UpdateProduct'`:
- These represent tier changes, stakeholder count increases, etc.
- Capture the ARR value at the time of the UpdateProduct event (pre-escalator)

**Key Detail:** We look for the first snapshot that appears *after* the UpdateProduct date but *before* the next renewal. This represents the "as_of_date" when the change takes effect in our mart.

### Step 3: Get Pre-Update ARR

For each UpdateProduct event, find the ARR value immediately *before* the update:
- Look backward in the snapshot history
- Get the most recent charge ARR before the UpdateProduct date

**Filter:** We exclude UpdateProduct events where there's no prior ARR history (these represent first-time subscriptions, not upgrades).

### Step 4: Calculate Organic Expansion

```
Organic Raw Expansion = UpdateProduct ARR - Pre-Update ARR
```

**Filters Applied:**
- Only include LLC subsidiary charges (`subsidiary = '100 - Carta - LLC'`)
- Exclude first-time subscriptions (where `pre_update_arr IS NULL`)
- Exclude zero-value changes (where `organic_expansion_dollars = 0`)
- Only include charges where `arr_dollars != 0`

### Step 5: Aggregate by Product

Sum organic expansion amounts for:
1. **Product-level:** Individual products (e.g., "LLC Cap Table", "LLC Transfer Agent")
2. **All LLC Products:** Rollup across all LLC products for a given account and date

---

## Data Sources

### Primary Source: Zuora Contract Subscriptions Snapshot
**Table:** `dbt_snapshots.core_dim_zuora_contract_subscriptions_snapshot`

**Key Fields:**
- `rate_plan_charge_id`: Unique charge identifier
- `subscription_id`: Zuora subscription ID
- `salesforce_account_id`: Customer account ID
- `product`: Product name
- `arr_dollars`: Annual recurring revenue for the charge
- `dbt_valid_from`: When the charge snapshot became active
- `dbt_valid_to`: When the charge snapshot became invalid (NULL if still active)
- `effective_start_date`: Contract effective start date
- `effective_end_date`: Contract effective end date

### Secondary Source: Zuora Subscriptions (Orders)
**Table:** `core_dim_zuora_subscriptions`

**Key Fields:**
- `order_type`: Type of order (we filter for 'UpdateProduct')
- `charge_number`: Links back to rate plan charges
- `effective_start_date`: When the order takes effect
- `created_at`: When the order was created in Zuora

---

## Output Granularity

**Grain:** One row per `(salesforce_account_id, product, charge_added_date)`

### Output Columns:
- `_pk`: Primary key (hash of account, product, date)
- `charge_added_date`: Date when the organic expansion occurred
- `salesforce_account_id`: Customer account
- `product`: Product name (or "All LLC Products")
- `total_pre_update_arr`: Total ARR before the UpdateProduct event
- `total_update_product_arr`: Total ARR from the UpdateProduct order
- `total_organic_expansion_dollars`: Calculated organic expansion (difference)

---

## Edge Cases Handled

### 1. First-Time Subscriptions
**Scenario:** Customer signs up for a new product  
**Handling:** Excluded via `pre_update_arr IS NOT NULL` filter  
**Rationale:** This is "New Business", not organic expansion

### 2. Multiple UpdateProduct Events Same Day
**Scenario:** Customer upgrades multiple charges on the same date  
**Handling:** Aggregated at the product level  
**Result:** Single row with summed organic expansion for that account-product-date

### 3. Renewal Between UpdateProduct Events
**Scenario:** Customer renews subscription after an UpdateProduct  
**Handling:** Use first renewal date as cutoff for finding snapshot  
**Rationale:** Ensures we capture the expansion at the right point in time

### 4. Charges with Zero ARR
**Scenario:** Rate plan charges with $0 ARR  
**Handling:** Excluded from source data  
**Rationale:** No revenue impact to track

### 5. Floating Point Precision
**Scenario:** ARR calculations with many decimals  
**Handling:** Accepted (differences typically < 0.00001)  
**Validation:** Components sum to total ARR delta within floating point precision

---

## Integration with Mart

The organic expansion model feeds into `mart_arr_zuora_delta_expansion_detailed_llc`:

```sql
-- Mart adds this column:
arr_delta_organic_raw_expansion

-- Joined on:
- salesforce_account_id
- product  
- as_of_date (matches charge_added_date from organic model)
```

### Mart Validation
Total ARR delta should equal the sum of components:
```
arr_delta_day = 
    arr_delta_escalator 
    + arr_delta_organic_raw_expansion 
    + arr_delta_total_discount_impact
```

**Current Results:**
- 7,710 total mart rows
- 1,269 rows with organic expansion (16.5%)
- All components sum correctly (validated ‚úÖ)

---

## Use Cases

### 1. Product Analytics
Track which products are seeing the most organic growth from customer upgrades.

### 2. Customer Success Metrics
Identify customers who are expanding their usage (good retention signal).

### 3. Revenue Attribution
Break down ARR changes into escalator vs. organic vs. discount components.

### 4. Sales Compensation
Potentially use organic expansion as a metric for account manager compensation.

### 5. Forecasting
Better predict ARR growth by separating organic expansion from contractual escalators.

---

## Example Query

```sql
-- Get top 10 accounts by organic expansion in 2025
SELECT 
    salesforce_account_id,
    product,
    SUM(total_organic_expansion_dollars) as total_organic_expansion,
    COUNT(*) as expansion_events
FROM prod_db.dbt_core.core_fct_zuora_arr_organic_expansion_llc
WHERE charge_added_date >= '2025-01-01'
GROUP BY 1, 2
ORDER BY 3 DESC
LIMIT 10;
```

---

## Limitations & Considerations

### 1. LLC Subsidiary Only
Currently only tracks LLC products. Other subsidiaries (Inc, International) would need separate models.

### 2. Pre-Escalator Values
Organic expansion is calculated *before* escalator pricing. The escalator component is tracked separately in `core_fct_zuora_arr_escalator_llc`.

### 3. Snapshot Dependency
Relies on daily snapshots being run consistently. Gaps in snapshot data could lead to missing expansion events.

### 4. UpdateProduct Events Only
Only captures expansion from Zuora UpdateProduct orders. Other expansion mechanisms (e.g., adding new products) are tracked differently.

### 5. Date Convention
Uses `charge_added_date + 1` to match mart's `as_of_date` convention (expansion shows up the day after it's added to the snapshot).

---

## Questions?

For technical questions about the model:
- **Model Location:** `models/models_scratch/core/zuora/intermediate/llc_decomp/`
- **Jira Ticket:** [DA-4049](https://carta1.atlassian.net/browse/DA-4049)
- **GitHub PR:** [#8938](https://github.com/carta/ds-dbt/pull/8938)

For business questions about organic expansion metrics:
- Contact: Data Analytics team or Product Analytics

Aha! So the escalator model has $245 escalator for this date. And our organic model is also calculating $245. This means we're double-counting.

The problem is that when an UpdateProduct event happens, it includes both:
1. The organic expansion (tier upgrade, more stakeholders, etc.)
2. The escalator charge that gets added at the same time

So UpdateProduct ARR = Pre-Update ARR + Organic Expansion + Escalator

But we're calculating:
Organic = UpdateProduct ARR - Pre-Update ARR
Which gives us: Organic Expansion + Escalator

Then in the mart we're adding escalator again, so we get:
Total = (Organic Expansion + Escalator) + Escalator = Organic Expansion + 2*Escalator

This is wrong. We need to subtract the escalator from the organic calculation. Let me check if we can get the escalator information during the organic calculation and subtract it out.

Actually, looking at the description from the yml file, it says the organic expansion should be "UpdateProduct ARR - Pre-Update ARR" and it says "before escalator is applied". But the UpdateProduct ARR is already including the escalator charge that gets added.

The fix is: we need to identify and subtract out the escalator component from the UpdateProduct ARR before calculating organic expansion.

SELECT
        rate_plan_charge_id
        , subscription_id
        , salesforce_account_id
        , salesforce_entity_id
        , product
        , rate_plan_name
        , charge_number
        , subsidiary
        , arr_dollars
        , MIN(charge_added_date) AS charge_added_date
        , MAX(charge_dropped_date) AS charge_dropped_date
    FROM grouped_with_numbers
    GROUP BY
        rate_plan_charge_id
        , subscription_id
        , salesforce_account_id
        , salesforce_entity_id
        , product
        , rate_plan_name
        , charge_number
        , subsidiary
        , group_number
        , arr_dollars
),

renewal_metadata AS (
    SELECT
        oa.type AS order_action_type
        , rpc.rate_plan_charge_id
        , rpc.price_increase_percentage AS price_increase_percent
        , rpc.cpq_renewal_price_c AS renewal_price
        , otcb.value
    FROM {{ ref('base_zuora_rate_plan_charge') }} rpc
    JOIN {{ ref('base_zuora_order_action') }} oa
        ON rpc.subscription_id = oa.subscription_id
    JOIN {{ ref('base_zuora_order_tcb') }} otcb
        ON rpc.rate_plan_charge_id = otcb.rate_plan_charge_id
    WHERE oa.type = 'RenewSubscription'
),

final_cte AS (
    SELECT
        fc.rate_plan_charge_id
        , fc.charge_added_date
        , fc.charge_dropped_date
        , fc.salesforce_account_id
        , fc.product
        , rm.order_action_type
        , rm.price_increase_percent
        , fc.arr_dollars
        , rm.renewal_price
        , rm.value
        , CASE 
            WHEN CEIL(ROUND(fc.arr_dollars, 2)) = CEIL(ROUND(rm.value, 2))
                OR ABS(CEIL(ROUND(fc.arr_dollars, 2)) - (CEIL(ROUND(rm.value, 2)) + CEIL(ROUND(rm.renewal_price, 2)))) <= 1
            THEN ROUND(rm.value - (rm.value / (1 + (rm.price_increase_percent / 100.0))), 2)
            ELSE NULL
          END AS escalator_dollars
    FROM final_charges fc
    JOIN renewal_metadata rm 
        ON fc.rate_plan_charge_id = rm.rate_plan_charge_id
    WHERE 
        CEIL(ROUND(fc.arr_dollars, 2)) = CEIL(ROUND(rm.value, 2))
        OR ABS(CEIL(ROUND(fc.arr_dollars, 2)) - (CEIL(ROUND(rm.value, 2)) + CEIL(ROUND(rm.renewal_price, 2)))) <= 1
),

final_cte_aggregated AS (
    SELECT
        charge_added_date
        , charge_dropped_date
        , salesforce_account_id
        , product
        , SUM(arr_dollars) AS total_arr_dollars
        , SUM(renewal_price) AS total_renewal_price
        , SUM(value) AS total_value
        , SUM(escalator_dollars) AS total_escalator_dollars
    FROM final_cte
    GROUP BY
        charge_added_date
        , charge_dropped_date
        , salesforce_account_id
        , product
),

all_products_grouping AS (
    SELECT
        charge_added_date
        , charge_dropped_date
        , salesforce_account_id
        , 'All LLC Products' AS product
        , SUM(total_arr_dollars) AS total_arr_dollars
        , SUM(total_renewal_price) AS total_renewal_price
        , SUM(total_value) AS total_value
        , SUM(total_escalator_dollars) AS total_escalator_dollars
    FROM final_cte_aggregated
    GROUP BY
        charge_added_date
        , charge_dropped_date
        , salesforce_account_id

content.thinking:
Perfect! Now I can see what happened:

**Oct 26 (before UpdateProduct):**
- Platform Fee: Stakeholders: $3,500
- Discount: -$525
- Net: $2,975

**Oct 27 (after UpdateProduct):**
- Platform Fee: Stakeholders: $3,745
- Discount: -$525
- Net: $3,220

**Change:**
- Platform Fee increased: $3,745 - $3,500 = $245

So the $245 is from the Platform Fee charge increasing. This charge went from $3,500 to $3,745.

Now the question is: is this $245 ALL escalator, or is it organic expansion + escalator?

Looking at the escalator model, it found $245 of escalator. So it seems like the entire $245 is escalator.

But our organic model is also calculating $245 as organic expansion.

The issue is clear now: when an escalator is applied (via an UpdateProduct event), our organic model sees:
- Pre-Update ARR: $3,500
- UpdateProduct ARR: $3,745
- Organic = $3,745 - $3,500 = $245

But this $245 is actually ALL escalator, not organic expansion. There's no true "organic" expansion here (no tier upgrade, no additional stakeholders added by the customer).

The fix is: we need to filter OUT escalator charges from our organic expansion calculation. We should only count UpdateProduct changes that are NOT purely escalator-driven.

Let me check if there's a way to identify escalator charges in the organic model.

I see - there are multiple UpdateProduct records for the same effective_start_date. The "Platform Fee: Stakeholders" charge has records showing both $3,500 and $3,745. This suggests that UpdateProduct event created a new version of the charge.

The key issue is: our organic expansion model is treating ANY change via UpdateProduct as "organic expansion", but in reality, when the only change is from an escalator (automatic price increase), that should NOT be counted as organic expansion.

The solution is: we need to subtract out the escalator component from our organic expansion calculation. We should modify the organic expansion model to:

1. Calculate the raw UpdateProduct change (as we do now)
2. Subtract any escalator amounts that occurred on the same date
3. Only keep the remainder as true organic expansion

Let me draft this fix.

content.text:
Found the issue. The organic expansion model is counting escalator-driven UpdateProduct events as organic expansion. When an escalator price increase happens, it triggers an UpdateProduct order, and we're calculating the entire ARR increase as "organic" when it's actually just escalator.

**Example:**
- Pre-Update ARR: $3,500
- Post-Update ARR: $3,745  
- Calculated Organic: $245
- But Escalator: $245
- **True Organic should be: $0** (no tier upgrade, just automatic price increase)

The fix: subtract escalator from organic expansion. Let me update the model:

{{ config(
    unique_key = '_pk',
    cluster_by = ['charge_added_date', 'salesforce_account_id', 'product']
) }}

-- Extract all rate plan charges from the snapshot for all LLC accounts
WITH base_data AS (
    SELECT
        rate_plan_charge_id
        , subscription_id
        , salesforce_account_id
        , salesforce_entity_id
        , product
        , rate_plan_name
        , charge_number
        , subsidiary
        , arr_dollars
        , effective_start_date
        , effective_end_date
        , dbt_valid_from::DATE AS charge_added_date
        , COALESCE(dbt_valid_to::DATE, effective_end_date::DATE) AS charge_dropped_date
    FROM {{ ref('core_dim_zuora_contract_subscriptions_snapshot') }}
    WHERE subsidiary = '100 - Carta - LLC'
        AND arr_dollars != 0
        AND salesforce_account_id IS NOT NULL
),

-- Add previous charge_dropped_date to identify gaps in charge history
ordered_data AS (
    SELECT
        *
        , LAG(charge_dropped_date) OVER (
            PARTITION BY rate_plan_charge_id
            ORDER BY charge_added_date
        ) AS prev_dropped_date
    FROM base_data
),

-- Flag when a new group starts (gap between prev_dropped_date and charge_added_date)
grouped_data AS (
    SELECT
        *
        , CASE 
            WHEN prev_dropped_date IS NULL 
                OR charge_added_date > prev_dropped_date THEN 1
            ELSE 0
          END AS is_new_group
    FROM ordered_data
),

-- Assign group numbers to continuous charge periods
grouped_with_numbers AS (
    SELECT
        *
        , SUM(is_new_group) OVER (
            PARTITION BY rate_plan_charge_id
            ORDER BY charge_added_date 
            ROWS UNBOUNDED PRECEDING
        ) AS group_number
    FROM grouped_data
),

-- Consolidate continuous charge periods into single records (matches escalator model logic)
final_charges AS (
    SELECT
        rate_plan_charge_id
        , subscription_id
        , salesforce_account_id
        , salesforce_entity_id
        , product
        , rate_plan_name
        , charge_number
        , subsidiary
        , arr_dollars
        , MIN(charge_added_date) AS charge_added_date
        , MAX(charge_dropped_date) AS charge_dropped_date
    FROM grouped_with_numbers
    GROUP BY
        rate_plan_charge_id
        , subscription_id
        , salesforce_account_id
        , salesforce_entity_id
        , product
        , rate_plan_name
        , charge_number
        , subsidiary
        , group_number
        , arr_dollars
),

-- Get all UpdateProduct order events with their ARR values (pre-escalator)
update_product_orders AS (
    SELECT
        z.rate_plan_charge_id
        , z.salesforce_account_id
        , z.product
        , z.charge_number
        , z.rate_plan_name
        , z.arr_dollars AS update_product_arr
        , z.effective_start_date AS update_date
        , z.created_at
        , z.order_type
    FROM {{ ref('core_dim_zuora_subscriptions') }} z
    WHERE z.order_type = 'UpdateProduct'
        AND z.subsidiary = '100 - Carta - LLC'
),

-- Find the first RenewSubscription event after each UpdateProduct to determine cutoff date
renewal_orders AS (
    SELECT
        z.charge_number
        , z.effective_start_date
        , MIN(z.created_at) AS first_renewal_at
    FROM {{ ref('core_dim_zuora_subscriptions') }} z
    WHERE z.order_type = 'RenewSubscription'
        AND z.subsidiary = '100 - Carta - LLC'
    GROUP BY z.charge_number, z.effective_start_date
),

-- Combine UpdateProduct with renewal timing to set search window for snapshot
update_with_renewal_date AS (
    SELECT
        up.*
        , COALESCE(ren.first_renewal_at::DATE, up.update_date + 30) AS renewal_cutoff_date
    FROM update_product_orders up
    LEFT JOIN renewal_orders ren
        ON up.charge_number = ren.charge_number
        AND up.update_date = ren.effective_start_date
),

-- Find the first snapshot added after UpdateProduct (determines as_of_date for mart)
snapshot_at_renewal AS (
    SELECT
        uwr.charge_number
        , uwr.update_date
        , uwr.renewal_cutoff_date
        , fc.charge_added_date
        , fc.charge_added_date + 1 AS as_of_date
    FROM update_with_renewal_date uwr
    JOIN final_charges fc
        ON uwr.charge_number = fc.charge_number
        AND fc.charge_added_date >= uwr.update_date
        AND fc.charge_added_date <= uwr.renewal_cutoff_date
    QUALIFY ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY uwr.charge_number, uwr.update_date ORDER BY fc.charge_added_date) = 1
),

-- Get ARR value immediately before the UpdateProduct event
pre_update_arr AS (
    SELECT
        uwr.charge_number
        , uwr.update_date
        , fc.arr_dollars AS pre_update_arr
    FROM update_with_renewal_date uwr
    JOIN final_charges fc
        ON uwr.charge_number = fc.charge_number
        AND fc.charge_dropped_date <= uwr.update_date
    QUALIFY ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY uwr.charge_number, uwr.update_date ORDER BY fc.charge_dropped_date DESC) = 1
),

-- Calculate organic_raw per charge: UpdateProduct ARR - Pre-Update ARR
organic_calculation AS (
    SELECT
        sar.as_of_date AS charge_added_date
        , up.salesforce_account_id
        , up.product
        , up.charge_number
        , up.rate_plan_name
        , pre.pre_update_arr
        , up.update_product_arr
        , up.update_product_arr - pre.pre_update_arr AS organic_expansion_dollars
    FROM update_with_renewal_date up
    JOIN snapshot_at_renewal sar
        ON up.charge_number = sar.charge_number
        AND up.update_date = sar.update_date
    LEFT JOIN pre_update_arr pre
        ON up.charge_number = pre.charge_number
        AND up.update_date = pre.update_date
    WHERE up.update_product_arr IS NOT NULL
        AND up.update_product_arr != 0
        AND pre.pre_update_arr IS NOT NULL
),

-- Aggregate organic expansion by product
product_level AS (
    SELECT
        charge_added_date
        , salesforce_account_id
        , product
        , SUM(pre_update_arr) AS total_pre_update_arr
        , SUM(update_product_arr) AS total_update_product_arr
        , SUM(organic_expansion_dollars) AS total_organic_expansion_dollars
    FROM organic_calculation
    GROUP BY charge_added_date, salesforce_account_id, product
),

-- Aggregate organic expansion for "All LLC Products"
all_products AS (
    SELECT
        charge_added_date
        , salesforce_account_id
        , 'All LLC Products' AS product
        , SUM(pre_update_arr) AS total_pre_update_arr
        , SUM(update_product_arr) AS total_update_product_arr
        , SUM(organic_expansion_dollars) AS total_organic_expansion_dollars
    FROM organic_calculation
    GROUP BY charge_added_date, salesforce_account_id
),

unioned_records AS (
    SELECT * FROM product_level
    WHERE total_organic_expansion_dollars != 0

    UNION ALL

    SELECT * FROM all_products
    WHERE total_organic_expansion_dollars != 0
)

SELECT
    {{ dbt_utils.generate_surrogate_key([
        'charge_added_date',
        'salesforce_account_id',
        'product'
    ]) }} AS _pk
    , charge_added_date
    , salesforce_account_id
    , product
    , total_pre_update_arr
    , total_update_product_arr
    , total_organic_expansion_dollars
FROM unioned_records
ORDER BY charge_added_date

        , SUM(update_product_arr) AS total_update_product_arr
        , SUM(true_organic_expansion) AS total_organic_expansion_dollars
    FROM organic_minus_escalator
    GROUP BY charge_added_date, salesforce_account_id
),

{{ config(
    unique_key = '_pk',
    cluster_by = ['charge_added_date', 'salesforce_account_id', 'product']
) }}

-- Extract all rate plan charges from the snapshot for all LLC accounts
WITH base_data AS (
    SELECT
        rate_plan_charge_id
        , subscription_id
        , salesforce_account_id
        , salesforce_entity_id
        , product
        , rate_plan_name
        , charge_number
        , subsidiary
        , arr_dollars
        , effective_start_date
        , effective_end_date
        , dbt_valid_from::DATE AS charge_added_date
        , COALESCE(dbt_valid_to::DATE, effective_end_date::DATE) AS charge_dropped_date
    FROM {{ ref('core_dim_zuora_contract_subscriptions_snapshot') }}
    WHERE subsidiary = '100 - Carta - LLC'
        AND arr_dollars != 0
        AND salesforce_account_id IS NOT NULL
),

-- Add previous charge_dropped_date to identify gaps in charge history
ordered_data AS (
    SELECT
        *
        , LAG(charge_dropped_date) OVER (
            PARTITION BY rate_plan_charge_id
            ORDER BY charge_added_date
        ) AS prev_dropped_date
    FROM base_data
),

-- Flag when a new group starts (gap between prev_dropped_date and charge_added_date)
grouped_data AS (
    SELECT
        *
        , CASE 
            WHEN prev_dropped_date IS NULL 
                OR charge_added_date > prev_dropped_date THEN 1
            ELSE 0
          END AS is_new_group
    FROM ordered_data
),

-- Assign group numbers to continuous charge periods
grouped_with_numbers AS (
    SELECT
        *
        , SUM(is_new_group) OVER (
            PARTITION BY rate_plan_charge_id
            ORDER BY charge_added_date 
            ROWS UNBOUNDED PRECEDING
        ) AS group_number
    FROM grouped_data
),

-- Consolidate continuous charge periods into single records (matches escalator model logic)
final_charges AS (
    SELECT
        rate_plan_charge_id
        , subscription_id
        , salesforce_account_id
        , salesforce_entity_id
        , product
        , rate_plan_name
        , charge_number
        , subsidiary
        , arr_dollars
        , MIN(charge_added_date) AS charge_added_date
        , MAX(charge_dropped_date) AS charge_dropped_date
    FROM grouped_with_numbers
    GROUP BY
        rate_plan_charge_id
        , subscription_id
        , salesforce_account_id
        , salesforce_entity_id
        , product
        , rate_plan_name
        , charge_number
        , subsidiary
        , group_number
        , arr_dollars
),

-- Get all UpdateProduct order events with their ARR values (pre-escalator)
update_product_orders AS (
    SELECT
        z.rate_plan_charge_id
        , z.salesforce_account_id
        , z.product
        , z.charge_number
        , z.rate_plan_name
        , z.arr_dollars AS update_product_arr
        , z.effective_start_date AS update_date
        , z.created_at
        , z.order_type
    FROM {{ ref('core_dim_zuora_subscriptions') }} z
    WHERE z.order_type = 'UpdateProduct'
        AND z.subsidiary = '100 - Carta - LLC'
),

-- Find the first RenewSubscription event after each UpdateProduct to determine cutoff date
renewal_orders AS (
    SELECT
        z.charge_number
        , z.effective_start_date
        , MIN(z.created_at) AS first_renewal_at
    FROM {{ ref('core_dim_zuora_subscriptions') }} z
    WHERE z.order_type = 'RenewSubscription'
        AND z.subsidiary = '100 - Carta - LLC'
    GROUP BY z.charge_number, z.effective_start_date
),

-- Combine UpdateProduct with renewal timing to set search window for snapshot
update_with_renewal_date AS (
    SELECT
        up.*
        , COALESCE(ren.first_renewal_at::DATE, up.update_date + 30) AS renewal_cutoff_date
    FROM update_product_orders up
    LEFT JOIN renewal_orders ren
        ON up.charge_number = ren.charge_number
        AND up.update_date = ren.effective_start_date
),

-- Find the first snapshot added after UpdateProduct (determines as_of_date for mart)
snapshot_at_renewal AS (
    SELECT
        uwr.charge_number
        , uwr.update_date
        , uwr.renewal_cutoff_date
        , fc.charge_added_date
        , fc.charge_added_date + 1 AS as_of_date
    FROM update_with_renewal_date uwr
    JOIN final_charges fc
        ON uwr.charge_number = fc.charge_number
        AND fc.charge_added_date >= uwr.update_date
        AND fc.charge_added_date <= uwr.renewal_cutoff_date
    QUALIFY ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY uwr.charge_number, uwr.update_date ORDER BY fc.charge_added_date) = 1
),

-- Get ARR value immediately before the UpdateProduct event
pre_update_arr AS (
    SELECT
        uwr.charge_number
        , uwr.update_date
        , fc.arr_dollars AS pre_update_arr
    FROM update_with_renewal_date uwr
    JOIN final_charges fc
        ON uwr.charge_number = fc.charge_number
        AND fc.charge_dropped_date <= uwr.update_date
    QUALIFY ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY uwr.charge_number, uwr.update_date ORDER BY fc.charge_dropped_date DESC) = 1
),

-- Calculate organic_raw per charge: UpdateProduct ARR - Pre-Update ARR
organic_calculation AS (
    SELECT
        sar.as_of_date AS charge_added_date
        , up.salesforce_account_id
        , up.product
        , up.charge_number
        , up.rate_plan_name
        , pre.pre_update_arr
        , up.update_product_arr
        , up.update_product_arr - pre.pre_update_arr AS organic_expansion_dollars
    FROM update_with_renewal_date up
    JOIN snapshot_at_renewal sar
        ON up.charge_number = sar.charge_number
        AND up.update_date = sar.update_date
    LEFT JOIN pre_update_arr pre
        ON up.charge_number = pre.charge_number
        AND up.update_date = pre.update_date
    WHERE up.update_product_arr IS NOT NULL
        AND up.update_product_arr != 0
        AND pre.pre_update_arr IS NOT NULL
),

-- Get escalator charges to subtract from organic expansion
escalator_charges AS (
    SELECT
        charge_added_date
        , salesforce_account_id
        , product
        , total_escalator_dollars
    FROM {{ ref('core_fct_zuora_arr_escalator_llc') }}
),

-- Subtract escalator from organic expansion to get true organic growth
organic_minus_escalator AS (
    SELECT
        oc.charge_added_date
        , oc.salesforce_account_id
        , oc.product
        , oc.charge_number
        , oc.rate_plan_name
        , oc.pre_update_arr
        , oc.update_product_arr
        , oc.organic_expansion_dollars
        , COALESCE(ec.total_escalator_dollars, 0) AS escalator_dollars
        , oc.organic_expansion_dollars - COALESCE(ec.total_escalator_dollars, 0) AS true_organic_expansion
    FROM organic_calculation oc
    LEFT JOIN escalator_charges ec
        ON oc.salesforce_account_id = ec.salesforce_account_id
        AND oc.product = ec.product
        AND oc.charge_added_date = ec.charge_added_date
),

-- Aggregate organic expansion by product
product_level AS (
    SELECT
        charge_added_date
        , salesforce_account_id
        , product
        , SUM(pre_update_arr) AS total_pre_update_arr
        , SUM(update_product_arr) AS total_update_product_arr
        , SUM(true_organic_expansion) AS total_organic_expansion_dollars
    FROM organic_minus_escalator
    GROUP BY charge_added_date, salesforce_account_id, product
),

-- Aggregate organic expansion for "All LLC Products"
all_products AS (
    SELECT
        charge_added_date
        , salesforce_account_id
        , 'All LLC Products' AS product
        , SUM(pre_update_arr) AS total_pre_update_arr
        , SUM(update_product_arr) AS total_update_product_arr
        , SUM(organic_expansion_dollars) AS total_organic_expansion_dollars
    FROM organic_calculation
    GROUP BY charge_added_date, salesforce_account_id
),

unioned_records AS (
    SELECT * FROM product_level
    WHERE total_organic_expansion_dollars != 0

    UNION ALL

    SELECT * FROM all_products
    WHERE total_organic_expansion_dollars != 0
)

SELECT
    {{ dbt_utils.generate_surrogate_key([
        'charge_added_date',
        'salesforce_account_id',
        'product'
    ]) }} AS _pk
    , charge_added_date
    , salesforce_account_id
    , product
    , total_pre_update_arr
    , total_update_product_arr
    , total_organic_expansion_dollars
FROM unioned_records
ORDER BY charge_added_date

{{ config(
    unique_key = '_pk',
    cluster_by = ['charge_added_date', 'salesforce_account_id', 'product']
) }}

-- Extract all rate plan charges from the snapshot for all LLC accounts
WITH base_data AS (
    SELECT
        rate_plan_charge_id
        , subscription_id
        , salesforce_account_id
        , salesforce_entity_id
        , product
        , rate_plan_name
        , charge_number
        , subsidiary
        , arr_dollars
        , effective_start_date
        , effective_end_date
        , dbt_valid_from::DATE AS charge_added_date
        , COALESCE(dbt_valid_to::DATE, effective_end_date::DATE) AS charge_dropped_date
    FROM {{ ref('core_dim_zuora_contract_subscriptions_snapshot') }}
    WHERE subsidiary = '100 - Carta - LLC'
        AND arr_dollars != 0
        AND salesforce_account_id IS NOT NULL
),

-- Add previous charge_dropped_date to identify gaps in charge history
ordered_data AS (
    SELECT
        *
        , LAG(charge_dropped_date) OVER (
            PARTITION BY rate_plan_charge_id
            ORDER BY charge_added_date
        ) AS prev_dropped_date
    FROM base_data
),

-- Flag when a new group starts (gap between prev_dropped_date and charge_added_date)
grouped_data AS (
    SELECT
        *
        , CASE 
            WHEN prev_dropped_date IS NULL 
                OR charge_added_date > prev_dropped_date THEN 1
            ELSE 0
          END AS is_new_group
    FROM ordered_data
),

-- Assign group numbers to continuous charge periods
grouped_with_numbers AS (
    SELECT
        *
        , SUM(is_new_group) OVER (
            PARTITION BY rate_plan_charge_id
            ORDER BY charge_added_date 
            ROWS UNBOUNDED PRECEDING
        ) AS group_number
    FROM grouped_data
),

-- Consolidate continuous charge periods into single records (matches escalator model logic)
final_charges AS (
    SELECT
        rate_plan_charge_id
        , subscription_id
        , salesforce_account_id
        , salesforce_entity_id
        , product
        , rate_plan_name
        , charge_number
        , subsidiary
        , arr_dollars
        , MIN(charge_added_date) AS charge_added_date
        , MAX(charge_dropped_date) AS charge_dropped_date
    FROM grouped_with_numbers
    GROUP BY
        rate_plan_charge_id
        , subscription_id
        , salesforce_account_id
        , salesforce_entity_id
        , product
        , rate_plan_name
        , charge_number
        , subsidiary
        , group_number
        , arr_dollars
),

-- Get all UpdateProduct order events with their ARR values (pre-escalator)
update_product_orders AS (
    SELECT
        z.rate_plan_charge_id
        , z.salesforce_account_id
        , z.product
        , z.charge_number
        , z.rate_plan_name
        , z.arr_dollars AS update_product_arr
        , z.effective_start_date AS update_date
        , z.created_at
        , z.order_type
    FROM {{ ref('core_dim_zuora_subscriptions') }} z
    WHERE z.order_type = 'UpdateProduct'
        AND z.subsidiary = '100 - Carta - LLC'
),

-- Find the first RenewSubscription event after each UpdateProduct to determine cutoff date
renewal_orders AS (
    SELECT
        z.charge_number
        , z.effective_start_date
        , MIN(z.created_at) AS first_renewal_at
    FROM {{ ref('core_dim_zuora_subscriptions') }} z
    WHERE z.order_type = 'RenewSubscription'
        AND z.subsidiary = '100 - Carta - LLC'
    GROUP BY z.charge_number, z.effective_start_date
),

-- Combine UpdateProduct with renewal timing to set search window for snapshot
update_with_renewal_date AS (
    SELECT
        up.*
        , COALESCE(ren.first_renewal_at::DATE, up.update_date + 30) AS renewal_cutoff_date
    FROM update_product_orders up
    LEFT JOIN renewal_orders ren
        ON up.charge_number = ren.charge_number
        AND up.update_date = ren.effective_start_date
),

-- Find the first snapshot added after UpdateProduct (determines as_of_date for mart)
snapshot_at_renewal AS (
    SELECT
        uwr.charge_number
        , uwr.update_date
        , uwr.renewal_cutoff_date
        , fc.charge_added_date
        , fc.charge_added_date + 1 AS as_of_date
    FROM update_with_renewal_date uwr
    JOIN final_charges fc
        ON uwr.charge_number = fc.charge_number
        AND fc.charge_added_date >= uwr.update_date
        AND fc.charge_added_date <= uwr.renewal_cutoff_date
    QUALIFY ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY uwr.charge_number, uwr.update_date ORDER BY fc.charge_added_date) = 1
),

-- Get ARR value immediately before the UpdateProduct event
pre_update_arr AS (
    SELECT
        uwr.charge_number
        , uwr.update_date
        , fc.arr_dollars AS pre_update_arr
    FROM update_with_renewal_date uwr
    JOIN final_charges fc
        ON uwr.charge_number = fc.charge_number
        AND fc.charge_dropped_date <= uwr.update_date
    QUALIFY ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY uwr.charge_number, uwr.update_date ORDER BY fc.charge_dropped_date DESC) = 1
),

-- Calculate organic_raw per charge: UpdateProduct ARR - Pre-Update ARR
organic_calculation AS (
    SELECT
        sar.as_of_date AS charge_added_date
        , up.salesforce_account_id
        , up.product
        , up.charge_number
        , up.rate_plan_name
        , pre.pre_update_arr
        , up.update_product_arr
        , up.update_product_arr - pre.pre_update_arr AS organic_expansion_dollars
    FROM update_with_renewal_date up
    JOIN snapshot_at_renewal sar
        ON up.charge_number = sar.charge_number
        AND up.update_date = sar.update_date
    LEFT JOIN pre_update_arr pre
        ON up.charge_number = pre.charge_number
        AND up.update_date = pre.update_date
    WHERE up.update_product_arr IS NOT NULL
        AND up.update_product_arr != 0
        AND pre.pre_update_arr IS NOT NULL
),

-- Get escalator charges to subtract from organic expansion
escalator_charges AS (
    SELECT
        charge_added_date
        , salesforce_account_id
        , product
        , total_escalator_dollars
    FROM {{ ref('core_fct_zuora_arr_escalator_llc') }}
),

-- Subtract escalator from organic expansion to get true organic growth
organic_minus_escalator AS (
    SELECT
        oc.charge_added_date
        , oc.salesforce_account_id
        , oc.product
        , oc.charge_number
        , oc.rate_plan_name
        , oc.pre_update_arr
        , oc.update_product_arr
        , oc.organic_expansion_dollars
        , COALESCE(ec.total_escalator_dollars, 0) AS escalator_dollars
        , oc.organic_expansion_dollars - COALESCE(ec.total_escalator_dollars, 0) AS true_organic_expansion
    FROM organic_calculation oc
    LEFT JOIN escalator_charges ec
        ON oc.salesforce_account_id = ec.salesforce_account_id
        AND oc.product = ec.product
        AND oc.charge_added_date = ec.charge_added_date
),

-- Aggregate organic expansion by product
product_level AS (
    SELECT
        charge_added_date
        , salesforce_account_id
        , product
        , SUM(pre_update_arr) AS total_pre_update_arr
        , SUM(update_product_arr) AS total_update_product_arr
        , SUM(true_organic_expansion) AS total_organic_expansion_dollars
    FROM organic_minus_escalator
    GROUP BY charge_added_date, salesforce_account_id, product
),

-- Aggregate organic expansion for "All LLC Products"
all_products AS (
    SELECT
        charge_added_date
        , salesforce_account_id
        , 'All LLC Products' AS product
        , SUM(pre_update_arr) AS total_pre_update_arr
        , SUM(update_product_arr) AS total_update_product_arr
        , SUM(true_organic_expansion) AS total_organic_expansion_dollars
    FROM organic_minus_escalator
    GROUP BY charge_added_date, salesforce_account_id
),

unioned_records AS (
    SELECT * FROM product_level
    WHERE total_organic_expansion_dollars != 0

    UNION ALL

    SELECT * FROM all_products
    WHERE total_organic_expansion_dollars != 0
)

SELECT
    {{ dbt_utils.generate_surrogate_key([
        'charge_added_date',
        'salesforce_account_id',
        'product'
    ]) }} AS _pk
    , charge_added_date
    , salesforce_account_id
    , product
    , total_pre_update_arr
    , total_update_product_arr
    , total_organic_expansion_dollars
FROM unioned_records
ORDER BY charge_added_date

content.thinking:
Oh no! Now the organic expansion is going negative, which makes things even worse. The difference is now even larger.

It looks like I'm subtracting escalator twice somehow. Let me think about this differently.

Actually, looking at the numbers:
- First row: escalator = 210, organic = -420
  - If organic was 210 before, and we subtracted 210 twice, we'd get: 210 - 210 - 210 = -210... no that doesn't work.
  - Actually: organic_before = 210, escalator = 210. After subtraction: 210 - 210 - 210 = -210? No wait.

Let me trace through the logic more carefully. The problem is that I'm aggregating at the product level AFTER subtracting escalator at the charge level. But escalator is already aggregated at the product level.

So if there are multiple charges for the same account/product/date:
- Charge 1: organic_expansion = 100, escalator (at product level) = 210
- Charge 2: organic_expansion = 110, escalator (at product level) = 210 (same value, joined multiple times)

After subtraction:
- Charge 1: 100 - 210 = -110
- Charge 2: 110 - 210 = -100
- Total: -110 + -100 = -210

But the correct logic should be:
- Total organic = 100 + 110 = 210
- Subtract escalator once: 210 - 210 = 0

So the issue is I'm joining escalator (which is already aggregated at product level) to individual charge-level records, causing the escalator to be subtracted multiple times.

The fix is to do the aggregation first, THEN subtract escalator.

content.text: I see the issue - I'm subtracting escalator at the charge level, but escalator is already aggregated at the product level. This causes escalator to be subtracted multiple times if there are multiple charges. Let me fix this:

toolUseResult.originalFile:
{{ config(
    unique_key = '_pk',
    cluster_by = ['charge_added_date', 'salesforce_account_id', 'product']
) }}

-- Extract all rate plan charges from the snapshot for all LLC accounts
WITH base_data AS (
    SELECT
        rate_plan_charge_id
        , subscription_id
        , salesforce_account_id
        , salesforce_entity_id
        , product
        , rate_plan_name
        , charge_number
        , subsidiary
        , arr_dollars
        , effective_start_date
        , effective_end_date
        , dbt_valid_from::DATE AS charge_added_date
        , COALESCE(dbt_valid_to::DATE, effective_end_date::DATE) AS charge_dropped_date
    FROM {{ ref('core_dim_zuora_contract_subscriptions_snapshot') }}
    WHERE subsidiary = '100 - Carta - LLC'
        AND arr_dollars != 0
        AND salesforce_account_id IS NOT NULL
),

-- Add previous charge_dropped_date to identify gaps in charge history
ordered_data AS (
    SELECT
        *
        , LAG(charge_dropped_date) OVER (
            PARTITION BY rate_plan_charge_id
            ORDER BY charge_added_date
        ) AS prev_dropped_date
    FROM base_data
),

-- Flag when a new group starts (gap between prev_dropped_date and charge_added_date)
grouped_data AS (
    SELECT
        *
        , CASE 
            WHEN prev_dropped_date IS NULL 
                OR charge_added_date > prev_dropped_date THEN 1
            ELSE 0
          END AS is_new_group
    FROM ordered_data
),

-- Assign group numbers to continuous charge periods
grouped_with_numbers AS (
    SELECT
        *
        , SUM(is_new_group) OVER (
            PARTITION BY rate_plan_charge_id
            ORDER BY charge_added_date 
            ROWS UNBOUNDED PRECEDING
        ) AS group_number
    FROM grouped_data
),

-- Consolidate continuous charge periods into single records (matches escalator model logic)
final_charges AS (
    SELECT
        rate_plan_charge_id
        , subscription_id
        , salesforce_account_id
        , salesforce_entity_id
        , product
        , rate_plan_name
        , charge_number
        , subsidiary
        , arr_dollars
        , MIN(charge_added_date) AS charge_added_date
        , MAX(charge_dropped_date) AS charge_dropped_date
    FROM grouped_with_numbers
    GROUP BY
        rate_plan_charge_id
        , subscription_id
        , salesforce_account_id
        , salesforce_entity_id
        , product
        , rate_plan_name
        , charge_number
        , subsidiary
        , group_number
        , arr_dollars
),

-- Get all UpdateProduct order events with their ARR values (pre-escalator)
update_product_orders AS (
    SELECT
        z.rate_plan_charge_id
        , z.salesforce_account_id
        , z.product
        , z.charge_number
        , z.rate_plan_name
        , z.arr_dollars AS update_product_arr
        , z.effective_start_date AS update_date
        , z.created_at
        , z.order_type
    FROM {{ ref('core_dim_zuora_subscriptions') }} z
    WHERE z.order_type = 'UpdateProduct'
        AND z.subsidiary = '100 - Carta - LLC'
),

-- Find the first RenewSubscription event after each UpdateProduct to determine cutoff date
renewal_orders AS (
    SELECT
        z.charge_number
        , z.effective_start_date
        , MIN(z.created_at) AS first_renewal_at
    FROM {{ ref('core_dim_zuora_subscriptions') }} z
    WHERE z.order_type = 'RenewSubscription'
        AND z.subsidiary = '100 - Carta - LLC'
    GROUP BY z.charge_number, z.effective_start_date
),

-- Combine UpdateProduct with renewal timing to set search window for snapshot
update_with_renewal_date AS (
    SELECT
        up.*
        , COALESCE(ren.first_renewal_at::DATE, up.update_date + 30) AS renewal_cutoff_date
    FROM update_product_orders up
    LEFT JOIN renewal_orders ren
        ON up.charge_number = ren.charge_number
        AND up.update_date = ren.effective_start_date
),

-- Find the first snapshot added after UpdateProduct (determines as_of_date for mart)
snapshot_at_renewal AS (
    SELECT
        uwr.charge_number
        , uwr.update_date
        , uwr.renewal_cutoff_date
        , fc.charge_added_date
        , fc.charge_added_date + 1 AS as_of_date
    FROM update_with_renewal_date uwr
    JOIN final_charges fc
        ON uwr.charge_number = fc.charge_number
        AND fc.charge_added_date >= uwr.update_date
        AND fc.charge_added_date <= uwr.renewal_cutoff_date
    QUALIFY ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY uwr.charge_number, uwr.update_date ORDER BY fc.charge_added_date) = 1
),

-- Get ARR value immediately before the UpdateProduct event
pre_update_arr AS (
    SELECT
        uwr.charge_number
        , uwr.update_date
        , fc.arr_dollars AS pre_update_arr
    FROM update_with_renewal_date uwr
    JOIN final_charges fc
        ON uwr.charge_number = fc.charge_number
        AND fc.charge_dropped_date <= uwr.update_date
    QUALIFY ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY uwr.charge_number, uwr.update_date ORDER BY fc.charge_dropped_date DESC) = 1
),

-- Calculate organic_raw per charge: UpdateProduct ARR - Pre-Update ARR
organic_calculation AS (
    SELECT
        sar.as_of_date AS charge_added_date
        , up.salesforce_account_id
        , up.product
        , up.charge_number
        , up.rate_plan_name
        , pre.pre_update_arr
        , up.update_product_arr
        , up.update_product_arr - pre.pre_update_arr AS organic_expansion_dollars
    FROM update_with_renewal_date up
    JOIN snapshot_at_renewal sar
        ON up.charge_number = sar.charge_number
        AND up.update_date = sar.update_date
    LEFT JOIN pre_update_arr pre
        ON up.charge_number = pre.charge_number
        AND up.update_date = pre.update_date
    WHERE up.update_product_arr IS NOT NULL
        AND up.update_product_arr != 0
        AND pre.pre_update_arr IS NOT NULL
),

-- Get escalator charges to subtract from organic expansion
escalator_charges AS (
    SELECT
        charge_added_date
        , salesforce_account_id
        , product
        , total_escalator_dollars
    FROM {{ ref('core_fct_zuora_arr_escalator_llc') }}
),

-- Subtract escalator from organic expansion to get true organic growth
organic_minus_escalator AS (
    SELECT
        oc.charge_added_date
        , oc.salesforce_account_id
        , oc.product
        , oc.charge_number
        , oc.rate_plan_name
        , oc.pre_update_arr
        , oc.update_product_arr
        , oc.organic_expansion_dollars
        , COALESCE(ec.total_escalator_dollars, 0) AS escalator_dollars
        , oc.organic_expansion_dollars - COALESCE(ec.total_escalator_dollars, 0) AS true_organic_expansion
    FROM organic_calculation oc
    LEFT JOIN escalator_charges ec
        ON oc.salesforce_account_id = ec.salesforce_account_id
        AND oc.product = ec.product
        AND oc.charge_added_date = ec.charge_added_date + 1
),

-- Aggregate organic expansion by product
product_level AS (
    SELECT
        charge_added_date
        , salesforce_account_id
        , product
        , SUM(pre_update_arr) AS total_pre_update_arr
        , SUM(update_product_arr) AS total_update_product_arr
        , SUM(true_organic_expansion) AS total_organic_expansion_dollars
    FROM organic_minus_escalator
    GROUP BY charge_added_date, salesforce_account_id, product
),

-- Aggregate organic expansion for "All LLC Products"
all_products AS (
    SELECT
        charge_added_date
        , salesforce_account_id
        , 'All LLC Products' AS product
        , SUM(pre_update_arr) AS total_pre_update_arr
        , SUM(update_product_arr) AS total_update_product_arr
        , SUM(true_organic_expansion) AS total_organic_expansion_dollars
    FROM organic_minus_escalator
    GROUP BY charge_added_date, salesforce_account_id
),

unioned_records AS (
    SELECT * FROM product_level
    WHERE total_organic_expansion_dollars != 0

    UNION ALL

    SELECT * FROM all_products
    WHERE total_organic_expansion_dollars != 0
)

SELECT
    {{ dbt_utils.generate_surrogate_key([
        'charge_added_date',
        'salesforce_account_id',
        'product'
    ]) }} AS _pk
    , charge_added_date
    , salesforce_account_id
    , product
    , total_pre_update_arr
    , total_update_product_arr
    , total_organic_expansion_dollars
FROM unioned_records
ORDER BY charge_added_date

I see - these rows have large ARR changes but NO organic expansion and NO escalator. This means these are likely:
1. New business (new subscriptions) - not upgrades
2. Churn/cancellations
3. Other types of expansion/contraction that aren't from UpdateProduct events

Our organic expansion model is specifically designed to capture UpdateProduct-driven expansion (tier upgrades, stakeholder increases). It was never meant to capture ALL expansion.

This is actually correct behavior! Not all ARR changes are due to organic expansion or escalator. There are other sources like:
- New subscriptions (new business)
- Cancellations (churn)
- Product additions (adding new products, not upgrading existing)
- Etc.

The original issue the user reported was about DOUBLE-COUNTING, where escalator + organic was MORE than the total delta. That's fixed now.

The fact that some rows don't fully decompose is expected - we're only decomposing the UpdateProduct-driven expansion and escalator portions. The remainder would be other types of changes.

content.thinking:
I see a pattern! In multiple rows:
- escalator = $997.50
- organic = -$997.50
- sum = $0
- But arr_delta_day = $997.50

So the organic is going NEGATIVE by the exact amount of the escalator, which means I'm subtracting escalator TWICE somehow. 

Wait, I think I see the issue. When I aggregate organic_expansion_dollars (which is UpdateProduct ARR - Pre-Update ARR), this ALREADY includes the escalator. So if:
- Pre-Update ARR = $10,000
- UpdateProduct ARR = $10,997.50 (includes $997.50 escalator added during the update)
- Organic (raw) = $10,997.50 - $10,000 = $997.50

Then I subtract escalator:
- Organic (adjusted) = $997.50 - $997.50 = $0

But the problem is that if this was ONLY an escalator event (no real organic expansion), then the UpdateProduct ARR shouldn't have included a real expansion, just the escalator. So the calculation should result in 0, which is correct.

But then why is the mart showing sum = 0 but delta_day = 997.50?

Oh wait - I think the issue is that in "All LLC Products" we're summing the product-level organic expansion AFTER subtracting escalator for each product. But "All LLC Products" escalator is its own separate value.

Let me re-examine my all_products logic.

content.text:
I see the issue - when calculating "All LLC Products", I'm subtracting the "All LLC Products" escalator from the sum of all product-level organic expansions, but those product-level organic expansions have ALREADY had their product-specific escalators subtracted. This causes escalator to be subtracted twice for the "All LLC Products" rollup.

The fix: For "All LLC Products", I should sum the ALREADY-ADJUSTED product-level organic expansions, not subtract escalator again. Let me update the model:

input.old_string:
-- Subtract escalator from all-products organic expansion
all_products AS (
    SELECT
        ap.charge_added_date
        , ap.salesforce_account_id
        , ap.product
        , ap.total_pre_update_arr
        , ap.total_update_product_arr
        , ap.total_organic_expansion_raw - COALESCE(ec.total_escalator_dollars, 0) AS total_organic_expansion_dollars
    FROM all_products_raw ap
    LEFT JOIN escalator_charges ec
        ON ap.salesforce_account_id = ec.salesforce_account_id
        AND ec.product = 'All LLC Products'
        AND ap.charge_added_date = ec.charge_added_date + 1
),
input.new_string:
-- For "All LLC Products", sum the already-adjusted product-level organic expansion
-- (don't subtract escalator again, as it was already subtracted at product level)
all_products AS (
    SELECT
        charge_added_date
        , salesforce_account_id
        , 'All LLC Products' AS product
        , SUM(total_pre_update_arr) AS total_pre_update_arr
        , SUM(total_update_product_arr) AS total_update_product_arr
        , SUM(total_organic_expansion_dollars) AS total_organic_expansion_dollars
    FROM product_level
    GROUP BY charge_added_date, salesforce_account_id
),

-- Extract all rate plan charges from the snapshot for all LLC accounts
WITH base_data AS (
    SELECT
        rate_plan_charge_id
        , subscription_id
        , salesforce_account_id
        , salesforce_entity_id
        , product
        , rate_plan_name
        , charge_number

        , effective_start_date
        , effective_end_date
        , dbt_valid_from::DATE AS charge_added_date
        , COALESCE(dbt_valid_to::DATE, effective_end_date::DATE) AS charge_dropped_date
    FROM {{ ref('core_dim_zuora_contract_subscriptions_snapshot') }}
    WHERE subsidiary = '100 - Carta - LLC'
        AND arr_dollars != 0
        AND salesforce_account_id IS NOT NULL
),

-- Add previous charge_dropped_date to identify gaps in charge history
ordered_data AS (
    SELECT
        *
        , LAG(charge_dropped_date) OVER (
            PARTITION BY rate_plan_charge_id
            ORDER BY charge_added_date
        ) AS prev_dropped_date
    FROM base_data
),

-- Flag when a new group starts (gap between prev_dropped_date and charge_added_date)
